history.origin: Diary of Walter Yonge of Colyton, Devon and MP for Honiton during the Long Parliament.
history.provenance: British Library catalogue: "The volume was apparently seized by the Royalists; see a note on f. 3: "This manuscript was founde by me one the 22th day of April, 1644, in the studie of Walter Younge, Esq., in his house of Studcombe [Stedeombe in Axminster] in Devon, witnes my haunde the day & yeare first aboue-written. E. Fortescue" [probably Sir Edmund Fortescue, the Royalist defender of Salcombe]. Phillipps MS. 20,757 (sale-cat. 1899, lot 340)".
